HOW TO CONFIGURE LAY:

Lay is tmux based. run "sudo nano $(which lay)" to configure the shell script. You can change pane arrangement, color, rc, everything!

- COMMANDS:
tks:
tks stands for tmux kill-server. It kills any running tmux sessions

lay:
starts Lay

lay-reinst:
removes tks, lay, tmux, and manpage, and reinstalls Lay from /usr/local/lib/lay

lay-reinst-alping
same as lay-reinst but for Alpine Linux

lay-uninst:
removes tks, lay, tmux, manpage, and the saved Lay clone (/usr/local/lib/lay)


